text: I can't believe someone would spend their time on this, but I must admit, I'm curious to see how accurate it is.
Haha, it's like Skynet, but for Kardashian baby names. We've come a long way in AI, haven't we?
To be fair, predicting the next Kardashian baby name is probably harder than predicting the stock market.
This is the pinnacle of human innovation right here. We've solved world hunger, climate change, and now... Kardashian baby names.
Don't forget flying cars and teleportation, but yeah, Kardashian baby names are the cherry on top.
I'm just waiting for the day when there's a baby named "Kwest." It's just a matter of time.
Hey, that's a great idea! Maybe we can use the same algorithm to predict the next Elon Musk baby name. It'll be like playing the lottery.
That would be an impressive feat. I can see it now: "AI Predicts Baby Names: From Kardashians to Musks" – that's a headline I'd click on.
It's all fun and games until the algorithm starts predicting your own baby names. Then it's just creepy.
"The Algorithm Has Chosen Your Baby Name: Resistance is Futile" – Sounds like a good premise for a Black Mirror episode.
I'd definitely watch that episode. Let's make it happen!
